==Ancient Greek==
===Etymology=== The most common uppercase form [[File:Greek uc omega.svg|x16px]] is a variant of omicron ({{l|grc|Ο|tr=-}}), broken up at the side ([[File:Greek Omega 09.svg|x16px]]), with the edges subsequently turned outward ([[File:Greek Omega 09.svg|x16px]], [[File:Greek Omega 05.svg|x16px]], [[File:Greek Omega 03.svg|x16px]], [[File:Greek Omega 07.svg|x16px]]). The alternative uppercase form, found in some typefaces, that looks like a larger version of lowercase {{l|grc|ω|tr=-}}, is from a digraph of two omicrons written close together.
===Letter=== {{head|grc|letter|uppercase||lowercase|ω}}
# The letter [[omega]] ({{l|grc|ὦ μέγα|tr=-}}), the 24th letter of the ancient [[Greek alphabet]].
